column1: Data Supplied By: National Livestock Reporting Service
Data source: National Livestock Reporting Service
Please see terms of use here: https://www.mla.com.au/general/Terms-and-conditions/data-and-information/

Blackall Agents penned 933 head at this weeks sale. All the regular processors feedlotters and backgrounders present. A mixed quality yarding of bullocks cows and light feeders and weaners.

 Light weight yearling steers under 200kg made from 334c to 340c/kg. Yearling steers 200 to 280kg also made to 340c/kg. Yearling steers 280 to 330kg topped 342c to average 322c/kg. Yearling steers 330 to 400kg averaged 275c and made to 324c/kg. Yearling steers 400 to 480kg made 320c/kg to restockers.

Light weight yearling heifers under 200kg sold from 156c to 194c/kg. Yearling heifers 200 to 280kg made to 222c/kg to feed. Yearling heifers 280 to 330kg lost ground selling to 222c/kg.

Manufacturing bullocks sold to 256c with the bullocks over 600kg selling to 262c/kg. Grown heifers over 540kg topped 246c with the majority selling from 196c to 226c/kg. The 2 score cows sold from 120c to 208c/kg. The 3 score cows sold to 212c/kg. The best of the heavy weight bulls to 236c/kg.

Market Reporter David Friend.
